    "Depending on the outcome of the actions, which include performing transactions, the agent is rewarded or penalised.",
    "For example, a successful transaction is rewarded and a fraud attempt is penalised.",
    "The next step is for the agent to learn an optimal strategy that helps it avoid fraud and maximise rewards.",
    "This approach allows the system to learn from its own experience and adapt to changing conditions to effectively detect fraud.",
    "A supervised learning method may be employed to categorise incoming customer service requests."
